/a> <span class=\"fn\">𝓧</span>)</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Basic.html#TopologicalSpace\">TopologicalSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝓧</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Tight.html#MeasureTheory.IsTightMeasureSet\">IsTightMeasureSet</a> <span class=\"fn\">S</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Iff\">↔</a> <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">ε</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/ENNReal/Basic.html#ENNReal\">ENNReal</a>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\">ε</span> → <span class=\"fn\">∃ (<span class=\"fn\">K</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#Set\">Set</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝓧</span></span>), <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Filter.html#IsCompact\">IsCompact</a> <span class=\"fn\">K</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <span class=\"fn\">∀ <span class=\"fn\">μ</span> ∈ <span class=\"fn\">S</span>, <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">μ</span> <span class=\"fn\">K</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Notation.html#Compl.compl\">ᶜ</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">ε</span></span></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"**Alias** of `MeasureTheory.isTightMeasureSet_iff_exists_isCompact_measure_compl_le`.\n\n---\n\nA set of measures `S` is tight if for all `0 < ε`, there exists a compact set `K` such that\nfor all `μ ∈ S`, `μ Kᶜ ≤ ε`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Tight.html#MeasureTheory.IsTightMeasureSet_iff_exists_isCompact_measure_compl_le","kind":"theorem","line":71,"name":"MeasureTheory.IsTightMeasureSet_iff_exists_isCompact_measure_compl_le","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathli