n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Basic.html#TopologicalSpace\">TopologicalSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝓧</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">S</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#Set\">Set</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/MeasureSpaceDef.html#MeasureTheory.Measure\">Measure</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝓧</span>)</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A set of measures `S` is tight if for all `0 < ε`, there exists a compact set `K` such that\nfor all `μ ∈ S`, `μ Kᶜ ≤ ε`.\nThis is formulated in terms of filters, and proven equivalent to the definition above\nin `IsTightMeasureSet_iff_exists_isCompact_measure_compl_le`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Tight.html#MeasureTheory.IsTightMeasureSet","kind":"def","line":51,"name":"MeasureTheory.IsTightMeasureSet","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Tight.lean#L51-L56"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Measure.ProbabilityMeasure","Mathlib.Topology.Metrizable.CompletelyMetrizable","Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Measure.LevyProkhorovMetric","Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Measure.RegularityCompacts"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Measure.Tight"}